  "source_id": "asthma-response-inhaled-steroids",
  "name": "Asthma Response to Inhaled Steroids",
  "description": "This test case evaluates identification of asthma patients who respond to inhaled corticosteroids (ICS). It requires finding patients aged 4-35 with at least 2 asthma diagnoses on different days, who have used inhaled corticosteroids during the specified age range, and have had inpatient hospitalizations with asthma exacerbations treated with oral/IV steroids. The phenotype also excludes patients with various comorbid conditions like cystic fibrosis, COPD, immunodeficiency, and other respiratory or systemic diseases that could confound asthma treatment response assessment.",
  "prompt": "Find patients aged 4-35 with asthma who have been treated with inhaled corticosteroids and have had hospitalizations requiring oral or IV steroids for asthma exacerbations.",
